Fix Qt 5.9.8 compatibility with newer MinGW-w64 headers that already define TOUCHINPUT

The original condition "defined(Q_CC_MINGW) || !defined(TOUCHEVENTF_MOVE)" always
includes the definitions when using MinGW, even if the system headers already provide
them. This causes redefinition errors with newer MinGW-w64 versions. The fix is to 
only define these structures when they're not already defined by the system headers.

--- old/qtbase/src/plugins/platforms/windows/qwindowsmousehandler.cpp
+++ new/qtbase/src/plugins/platforms/windows/qwindowsmousehandler.cpp
@@ -59,7 +59,7 @@
  * are present in the Windows SDK's, but not in older MSVC Express
  * versions. */
 
-#if defined(Q_CC_MINGW) || !defined(TOUCHEVENTF_MOVE)
+#if !defined(TOUCHEVENTF_MOVE)
 
 typedef struct tagTOUCHINPUT {
     LONG x;
